      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Half-length shot of a man sitting on a chair. He is wearing a dark suit.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Bogdan Popović (1863, Belgrade – 1944, Belgrade) was professor of Literary History and Theory at Belgrade's Grande École and later professor of French, History, Literature, Literary Theory and Aesthetics at the University of Belgrade. In 1901 he founded "Srpski knijževni glasnik" (Serbian literary journal), the most influental Serbian literary journal. He was also a member of the "Ujedinjenje" (unification) Masonic Lodge, which was formed in Belgrade in 1909. The photograph was a gift to his friend Milorad (Gavrilović).</ab>
